# JavaScript Standards

## Syntax
- Use `const`/`let`; never `var`
- Prefer arrow functions for callbacks; named functions for components/handlers
- Use optional chaining (`?.`) and nullish coalescing (`??`) where appropriate
- Use template literals for string interpolation

## Imports
- Group: React first, then third-party, then internal (`@/`), then relative
- Use path alias: `import { Button } from '@/components/ui/button'`

## Async / Promises
- Prefer `async/await` over raw `.then()`
- Always handle errors in try/catch; never swallow silently
- Use `useCallback` for async handlers passed to children or effects

## Examples
```javascript
// ✅ GOOD
const fetchData = useCallback(async () => {
  try {
    const snap = await getDocs(collection(db, 'Users'));
    return snap.docs.map(d => ({ id: d.id, ...d.data() }));
  } catch (error) {
    trackError('FETCH_ERROR', error.message, 'ComponentName');
    throw error;
  }
}, []);
```
